(89, NULL, 1, 'single', 'single', 'AIR\'N OUTDOOR', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'airn-outdoor', '1661845770462906427', 6, 0, 0, 80, '', 'unnamed-ihoLdGdIeDu5QAD8W9uVXBpop2P2IxM92id3v84g.png', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'https://airn.ch', NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'en', '2022-08-30 07:49:30', '2022-08-30 07:50:00'),
(90, '2022-09-09', 1, 'single', 'single', 'Seven Summit Treks (SST) Autumn 2022 Biggest Manaslu Expedition Begins', 'Seven Summit Treks (SST) Autumn 2022 Biggest Manaslu Expedition Begins', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Seven Summit Treks (SST) Autumn 2022 Expeditions have already begun where most of the climbers and Sherpa guides have reached the base camp and some of them have already started acclimatization rotation at a higher altitude. SST is organizing the expeditions in multiple mountains for more than 350 individuals including, more than a hundred climbing members, experienced Sherpa guides, High Altitude Workers, Cooks, and Kitchen Staff.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"https://www.sevensummittreks.com/storage/photos/1/Manaslu/manaslu-mid.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1200\" height=\"900\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">All teams in Manaslu are well settled in base camp and are in good shape. The teams will start to make their way to the summit from the 3<sup>rd</sup> week of September. Manaslu alone has almost 100 climbing members who will attempt to reach the real summit this Autumn. Similarly, we have a strong team in Mt. Dhaulagiri as well. The team will start to make their way to the summit of Dhaulagiri from the 4<sup>th</sup> week of September. Some of our members will be doing double 8000ers, first to Manaslu and then Dhaulagiri.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"https://www.sevensummittreks.com/storage/photos/1/Manaslu/manaslu-mid-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1200\" height=\"751\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Seven Summit Treks, established by four mountaineer brothers, is a Nepalese adventure operator, specializing in 8000ers and offers the major logistics in the Himalayas and Karakoram. We have guides, Sherpas, and leaders who have years of experience tussling with nature and then befriending it. We are proud to acknowledge that, our guides are people who find pleasure in the wide embrace of nature and they keep the safety of our clients, which is their number one priority.</p>', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Seven Summit Treks (SST) Autumn 2022 Biggest Manaslu Expedition Begins</p>', 'seven-summit-treks-sst-autumn-2022-biggest-manaslu-expedition-begins', '166313012358647885', 5, 0, 0, 11, 'banner-manaslu-rsyDEgx9UzakuHVMuBBaWDXGUiS981ZPHOvbtUPW.jpg', 'manaslu-thumbnail-wfdiosPal3AeKmkXUKfHY9MeCPC6li8QJqXPK2ve.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'en', '2022-09-14 04:35:23', '2022-09-15 07:16:22'),
(91, '2022-09-28', 1, 'single', 'single', 'SST Manaslu Expedition Summit Update!!', NULL, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">28.09.2022 SST Manaslu Expedition Summit Update!!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A huge congratulation to our team members and sherpa guide who have successfully reached the main summit of Mt. Manaslu (8163m) - the 8<sup>th</sup> highest mountain.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The members and guides made it to the main summit of Mt. Manaslu although the weather was severely harsh for climbing for most of the time during the expedition. After the avalanche between C3 to C4, most of the members returned to base camp from Camp 3.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Summiteer List (28.09.2022):</strong></p>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>Rouhollah Kazemi</li>\r\n<li>Benjamin Jonathon Rose</li>\r\n<li>Ming Temba Sherpa</li>\r\n<li>Gelu Sherpa</li>\r\n<li>Sajid Ali (summited on 27.09.2022 without the use of supplement oxygen)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Stay tuned for more summit updates.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Most of the members are already in higher camps waiting for the good weather window for the summit push. The rest of the teams are in good shape in Basecamp. This autumn SST is organizing the Manaslu expedition for more than 350 individuals including around 100 members.</p>', '<p>SST Manaslu Expedition Summit Update #1!!</p>', 'sst-manaslu-expedition-summit-update', '1664362978648179664', 5, 0, 0, 12, 'banner-summit-update-NTxyaETpHFQhWsgFYbCWfSbfHHTCTliGsL2n5FOe.jpg', 'manaslu-summait-cVHfP4Orv8PTSX2liSYk9f2F5o6jRzhI7wpBTVkx.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'en', '2022-09-28 11:02:58', '2022-09-30 07:20:19'),
(92, '2022-09-30', 1, 'single', 'single', 'Nima Rinji Sherpa - Youngest ever to climb the main summit of Mt. Manaslu', NULL, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A huge congratulation to our team members and sherpa guide who have successfully reached the main summit of Mt. Manaslu (8163m) - the 8<sup>th</sup> highest mountain this morning.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The members and guides made it to the main summit of Mt. Manaslu although the weather was severely harsh for climbing for most of the time during the expedition.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We are proud to announce that Nima Rinji Sherpa (16 years 5 months 12 days) became the youngest person to reach the main summit of Mt. Manaslu (8163m) - the 8<sup>th</sup> Highest mountain in the world.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"http://www.sevensummittreks.com/storage/photos/1/Manaslu/mid.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Summiteer List:</p>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>Nima Rinji Sherpa (Youngest ever to climb the main summit of Mt. Manaslu)</li>\r\n<li>Naoko Watanabe</li>\r\n<li>Tenjing Sherpa aka Lama</li>\r\n<li>Ahmad M. Saleh</li>\r\n<li>Manish Maharjan</li>\r\n<li>Pemba Thinduk Sherpa</li>\r\n<li>Nurbu Sherpa</li>\r\n<li>Lakpa Sherpa</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Stay tuned for more summit updates.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Most of the members are already in higher camps waiting for the good weather window for the summit push. The rest of the teams are in good shape in Basecamp. This autumn SST is organizing the Manaslu expedition for more than 350 individuals including around 100 members.</p>', '<p>SST Manaslu Expedition Summit Update #2!!</p>', 'nima-rinji-sherpa-youngest-ever-to-climb-the-main-summit-of-mt-manaslu', '1664522242668032501', 5, 0, 0, 13, 'manaslu-2-banner-lz02UOxRwzrWXvYRBlaV9VLuFtkbqg5ztHqyoWDq.jpg', 'manaslu-2-thumbnail-71VNHr5tkh001C8iWna7ElKkaTlwVrtB3e2ZZ0AD.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'en', '2022-09-30 07:17:22', '2022-09-30 07:26:39'),
(93, '2022-10-17', 1, 'single', 'single', 'Ama Dablam Rope Fixing Summit Update!!', NULL, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Ama Dablam Rope Fixing Summit Update!!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A team of Sherpa guides from Seven Summit Treks under the management of EOA (Expedition Operator Association of Nepal) successfully fixed the summit lines to the top of Mt. Ama Dablam (6812m) this late afternoon.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The team had continuously worked for 12 days in the high altitude before making it to the summit. Moreover, more than 400 clients and additional Sherpas will be engaged from different expedition teams to climb Ama Dablam this autumn.</p>', '<p>Ama Dablam Rope Fixing Summit Update!!</p>', 'ama-dablam-rope-fixing-summit-update', '166608442970079836', 5, 0, 0, 14, 'ama1-b-R2FurQ6NKdJrfjdCzIPfykNJOQntkekKRKSIKuLu.jpg', 'ama1-t-HcUJRGiKWivUfSeRsLjLwNsk8MOzdPs6Dd7x0SAX.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'en', '2022-10-18 09:13:49', '2022-10-18 09:16:19'),
(94, '2022-10-26', 1, 'single', 'single', 'SST Himlung Himal Summit Update', NULL, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">SST Himlung Autumn Expedition 2022 has come to the end with success. A huge congratulations to all the members and guides for the successful ascent of Himlung on 25 Oct 2022.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Summiteer List:</p>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>Nuri Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n<li>Pedro Jose Garcia Aguirre (Spain)</li>\r\n<li>Francisco Javier Urrate Riallos (Spain)</li>\r\n<li>Michaela Harasta (Germany)</li>\r\n<li>Matteo Sotti (Italy)</li>\r\n<li>Michele Cucchi (Italy)</li>\r\n<li>Tendi Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n<li>Ngima Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n<li>Chhiring Bhote (Nepal)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you want to experience climbing a 7000m peak and an excellent prior peak for 8000m expeditions - Join our Himlung Himal Expedition in the 2023 Autumn (Oct - Nov).</p>', '<p>SST Himlung Himal Summit Update</p>', 'sst-himlung-himal-summit-update', '1669537172335320620', 5, 0, 0, 15, 'himlung-bannner-13x2V1pIOv0g3CdTLWMhlFJgASnFe8MtEXlQqcnb.jpg', 'himlung-update-xkw0UucLwxoMOuMMhovA7WFyO2ud4lLuP6mFiaeQ.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'en', '2022-11-27 08:19:32', '2022-11-28 03:50:44'),
