(119, '2023-09-28', 1, 'single', 'single', 'Government of Nepal honors Seven Summit Treks as the largest taxpayer trekking company', 'Government of Nepal honors Seven Summit Treks as the largest taxpayer trekking company', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Kathmandu, Sept 28: The Government of Nepal has honored Seven Summit Treks (SST) for being the largest taxpayer trekking and expedition agency in Nepal. Minister for Tourism, Culture, and Civil Aviation Sudan Kirati handed the award to SST director Chhang Dawa Sherpa amid a function organized here on the occasion of World Tourism Day, 2023. Besides bringing in hundreds of mountaineers, SST paid 4.3 million USD in tax to the Government of Nepal in the fiscal year, 2022/23, being the largest taxpayer trekking and expedition company in the country. &nbsp;This is the 11<sup>th</sup> consecutive time since 2012 that Seven Summit Treks has been recognized as the largest revenue contributor trekking firm.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"http://www.sevensummittreks.com/storage/photos/1/award.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&ldquo;We are proud that we have received the honor for our contribution to the tourism sector and economy of the country as a whole. We are happy that we are able to bring lots of tourists to Nepal and have contributed a tax of USD 4.3 million directly to the government last FY,&rdquo; said SST Chairperson Mingma Sherpa.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">SST has significantly contributed to the trekking and expedition industry in Nepal, and remains committed to promoting high-altitude adventure tourism in the Himalayan and Karakoram regions in the world, he added.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">SST truly believes in the importance of making tourism accessible to all, and continues working to achieve this goal, said SST director Chhang Dawa. Mingma is the first Nepali and South Asian climber, who successfully ascended all 14 mountains of the world that are above 8,000m. Chhang Dawa is the second Nepali climber, who successfully summited 14 mountains of the world that are above 8,000m.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Based in Kathmandu, SST has been dedicated to promoting adventure tourism in Nepal since its inception in 2010. Established by four Sherpa brothers, SST specializes in trekking and expeditions. For the past 20 years, it has been organizing expeditions in Everest, Kanchenjunga, Makalu, Manaslu, and Annapurna, and treks in Annapurna, Khumbu, Langtang, Manang, Manaslu and so on. Besides, it offers major logistics in the Himalayan.</p>', '<p>Government of Nepal honors Seven Summit Treks as the largest taxpayer trekking company&nbsp;</p>', 'government-of-nepal-honors-seven-summit-treks-as-the-largest-taxpayer-trekking-company', '1695960569885516175', 5, 0, 0, 35, 'banner1-vYMHrJYkyZqlZb8ljb50mESv9VLMcbrxFr0MdRdy.jpg', 'thumbnail1-jIpQek9ZTdd3OcWN1LetSfkJhfTvFBzuCv9ElJlV.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Government of Nepal honors Seven Summit Treks as the largest taxpayer trekking company&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'en', '2023-09-29 04:09:29', '2023-09-29 04:22:06'),
(120, '2023-09-29', 1, 'single', 'single', 'SST team completes rope fixing on Dhaulagiri I opening route for climbers for Autumn 2023 season', 'SST team completes rope fixing on Dhaulagiri I opening route for climbers for Autumn 2023 season', '<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 15pt; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Segoe UI\',sans-serif;\">A team from Seven Summit Treks (SST), a Kathmandu-based trekking and expedition company, has completed fixing ropes from the Base Camp to the summit of Dhaulagiri I for this climbing season. The 13-member team, including nine regular climbers, fixed the ropes. It took two weeks for the task, and they used more than 7500 meters, said the director of SST, Chhang Dawa Sherpa.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 15pt 0cm; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Segoe UI\',sans-serif;\">After the completion of rope fixing, climbing a mountain formally begins. Rope fixing takes place every climbing season for the convenience of climbers. Ropes on mountains help mountaineers, guides, and porters climb frozen slopes when attempting a mountain.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 15pt 0cm; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Segoe UI\',sans-serif;\">The rope fixing members to the top of Dhaulagiri I are Mingma Sherpa (Nepal), Nima Rinji Sherpa (Nepal), Tenjen Sherpa aka Lama (Nepal), Mingtemba Sherpa (Nepal), Pasang Nurbu Sherpa (Nepal), Alina Pekova (Russia), Alasdair Mckenzie (France), Hoeskuldur Tryggvason (Iceland), Moeses Fiamoncini (Brazil), Pasang Dawa Sherpa (Nepal), Nangba Sherpa (Nepal), Mingma Nurbu Sherpa (Nepal), and Pemba Dorchi Sherpa (Nepal).</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Segoe UI\',sans-serif;\">Mingma Sherpa is the first Nepali and South Asian climber who successfully ascended all 14 mountains of the world that are above 8,000 meters. </span></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Segoe UI\',sans-serif;\">Nima Rinji Sherpa has successfully climbed nine mountains of the world above 8,000 meters. </span></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Segoe UI\',sans-serif;\">Tenjen ascended 14 peaks of the world in 92 days.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Segoe UI\',sans-serif;\">Mingtemba, Pasang Nurbu and Moeses Fiamoncini climbed the peak without using artificial supplementary oxygen.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 15pt 0cm 0cm; text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Segoe UI\',sans-serif;\">As of now, more than 650 ascents to the true summit of Dhaulagiri have been recorded.</span></p>', '<p>SST team completes rope fixing on Dhaulagiri I opening route for climbers for Autumn 2023 season</p>', 'sst-team-completes-rope-fixing-on-dhaulagiri-i-opening-route-for-climbers-for-autumn-2023-season', '1696038395645422469', 5, 0, 0, 36, '', 'dhau-thumbnail-znsq3dwsivx1oz3tv9wqmgij4yk57tut6wjuzwpn-X1S7VnLGiTos6l1m53ia9GDucfRmk3jmSPtVQ3Xu.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>SST team completes rope fixing on Dhaulagiri I opening route for climbers for Autumn 2023 season</p>', NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'en', '2023-09-30 01:46:35', '2023-09-30 01:56:02'),
(121, '2023-09-30', 1, 'single', 'single', 'Mountain guide Bhote becomes the first Nepali to ski from the summit of Mt. Manaslu', 'Mountain guide Bhote becomes the first Nepali to ski from the summit of Mt. Manaslu', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Kathmandu, Sept 30: Renowned mountain guide Tshering Pande Bhote climbed the 8161m peak of Manaslu and skied down from the summit, becoming the first Nepali climber to ski down the top of a mountain above 8000m.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The 45-year-old IFMGA certified mountain guide (instructor) from Bhotkhola-3, Sankhuwasabha district, reached the world&rsquo;s eighth highest peak on 21 September 2023 at 10:37 am Nepal time. Bhote did the expedition through the Seven Summit Treks (SST), a Kathmandu-based trekking and expedition company. He has a large career portfolio.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Bhote, an eminent personality in the mountaineering sector, was the first Nepali to acquire an International Federation of Mountain Guides Associations (IFMGA) guide accreditation apart from being one of the few people to hold certifications from both the New Zealand Mountain Guides Association (NZMGA) and the Nepal National Mountain Guides Association (NNMGA). He started his mountaineering career in 1996, he has so far successfully guided mountaineers to numerous mountains above 8000m including Everest, Cho Oyu, Shishapangma, Manaslu, Dhaulagiri, Makalu, and Lhotse.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A licensed rescue technician, he was one of the three mountain guides sent by Simrik Air to Zermatt, Switzerland in 1012 for specific Helicopter Rescue Specialist training. He has strong international climbing and rescue experience and extensive knowledge of logistics and planning. He is also the first RECCO instructor from Nepal.</p>', '<p><strong>Mountain guide Bhote becomes the first Nepali to ski from the summit of Mt. Manaslu &nbsp;</strong></p>', 'mountain-guide-bhote-becomes-the-first-nepali-to-ski-from-the-summit-of-mt-manaslu', '1696133194707524414', 5, 0, 0, 37, 'tshering-banner-VL3U7yJbaL7P1GfJnKPZoek8y8Tev3l8Ju4wNqEW.jpg', 'tshering-thumbnail-4mGA5NNgwUvxAuVxhxILkQA8mq2yUVfjohCJjiPQ.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><strong>Mountain guide Bhote becomes the first Nepali to ski from the summit of Mt. Manaslu &nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'en', '2023-10-01 04:06:34', '2023-10-01 04:07:00'),
(122, '2023-09-30', 1, 'single', 'single', 'SST records the highest summit success on Mt Manaslu in Autumn 2023', 'SST records the highest summit success on Mt Manaslu in Autumn 2023', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Kathmandu, Sep 30: The Seven Summit Treks (SST), a pioneering Kathmandu-based trekking and expedition company, has managed more than 113 summiteers to Mt. Manaslu (8163m), the world&rsquo;s eighth highest peak, for this Autumn climbing season in September 2023 alone. Most of the expeditions had taken place through the Seven Summit Treks and others through its sister organizations - 14 Peaks Expedition and Global Expedition.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Established by four Sherpa brothers, who themselves are mountaineers and have set multiple climbing records, SST has significantly contributed to the trekking and expedition industry in Nepal and remains committed to promoting high-altitude adventure tourism in the Himalayan and Karakoram regions in the world.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">SST has been dedicated to promoting adventure tourism in Nepal since its inception in 2010. It specializes in trekking and expeditions. For the past 20 years, it has been organizing expeditions in 8000ers of Nepal, China, and Pakistan. Besides, it offers major logistics in the Himalayan.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>About</u></strong><u> <strong>Manaslu</strong></u></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Manaslu also known as Kutang lies in the Mansiri Himal in the west-central part of Nepal. Manaslu means &lsquo;mountain of the spirit&rsquo;. It is also known as the &lsquo;Killer Mountain of the World&rsquo; due to the high fatality rate of climbers and the avalanche risks. The mountain was first climbed on 9 May 1956 by Toshio Imanishi and Gyalzen Norbu, members of a Japanese expedition. Manaslu, the highest peak in Gorkha district, is 64 km east of Annapurna.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Manaslu region offers a variety of trekking options. The popular Manaslu trekking route of 177 km goes around the Manaslu massif over the pass down to Annapurna. It takes approximately 65 days to climb the peak.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The entry point for the peak is through Dhadingbesi or Gorkha. There are two routes for Mt Manaslu. One begins from Gorkha to the Base Camp through Kalanchowk, Deurali, Gumda, Jagat, Philim, Bihi, Namrung, and Samagaun. The other starts from Dhadingbesi through Arughat, Jagat, Philim, Bihi, Namrung and Samagaun. The total distance of the Gorkha route is 120.6 km, and Dhadingbesi is 120.1 km.</p>\r\n<p><strong><u>List of Summiteers through SST and its sister organizations:</u></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>20 SEP 2023</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>SHEHROZE KASHIF (PAKISTAN)</li>\r\n<li>FLUTURA IBRAHIMI (ALBANIA)</li>\r\n<li>ADRIAN LAZA (ROMANIA)</li>\r\n<li>DOROTA LIDIA RASINSKA-SAMOCKO (POLAND)</li>\r\n<li>ALASDAIR SCOT MCKENZIE (FRANCE)</li>\r\n<li>ALINA PEKOVA (RUSSIA)</li>\r\n<li>MOESES FIAMONCINI (BRAZIL)</li>\r\n<li>TENJEN SHERPA (MAKALU-9, SANKHUWASABHA)</li>\r\n<li>CHHEPAL SHERPA (PATLE-2, OKHALDHUNGA)</li>\r\n<li>TENJING SHERPA (MAKALU-4, SANKHUWASABHA)</li>\r\n<li>DAWA NURBU SHERPA (MAKALU-9, SANKHUWASABHA)</li>\r\n<li>MINGTEMBA SHERPA (MAKALU-9, SANKHUWASABHA) - NO O2</li>\r\n<li>LAKPA NURBU SHERPA (MAKALU-5, SANKHUWASABHA)</li>\r\n<li>PASANG DAWA SHERPA (MAKALU-9, SANKHUWASABHA)</li>\r\n<li>PASANG NURBU SHERPA (MAKALU-9, SANKHUWASABHA) - NO O2</li>\r\n<li>MINGMA SHERPA (MAKALU-9, SANKHUWASABHA)</li>\r\n<li>LAKPA THENDU SHERPA (MAKALU-2, SANKHUWASABHA)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong>22 SEP 2023</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>ANDREY KAZAKOV (RUSSIA) - NO O2</li>\r\n<li>CHINJUNG BHOTE (HATIYA-1, SANKHUWASABHA)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong>23 SEP 2023</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>JAROSLAW ZDANOWICZ (POLAND) - NO O2</li>\r\n<li>LUKASZ LAGORZNY (POLAND) - NO O2</li>\r\n<li>STEPHANE, JEAN, LUCIEN PFEND (FRANCE)</li>\r\n<li>KENDALL DOUGLAS 