(136, '2024-03-01', 1, 'single', 'single', 'Heli Marshall and Safety Training for Sherpas: Preparing for Spring Expeditions', NULL, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">On March 1, 2024, at Tribhuvan International Airport, Seven Summit Treks (SST) is gearing up for an exhilarating spring season. SST, in collaboration with Heli Everest Pvt. Ltd., has organized a comprehensive Heli Marshall and Safety Training for its Sherpa team. A team of 34 field and operational crew of SST received the training supervised by Mr. Sachit Aryal. The instructors\' panel consisted of Er. Sumod Pokharel, Senior Captain Suraj Thapa, Training coordinator Mr. Pradin Kumar Gautam, proficient in heli operations and management. This training, scheduled just before the Spring Expeditions 2024, aims to enhance the skills and preparedness of our Sherpas who will be venturing into the high mountains.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The upcoming spring promises an array of challenging expeditions to some of the world&rsquo;s highest peaks, Everest, Kanchenjunga, Makalu,&nbsp; Dhaulagiri,&nbsp; Annapurna, and Sishapangma. Additionally, SST will lead expeditions to several 7000-meter and 6000-meter peaks, providing a wide variety of climbing options for mountaineers.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"http://www.sevensummittreks.com/storage/photos/1/General/6.JPG\" alt=\"\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>The Importance of Heli Marshall and Helicopter Safety Training</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Heli Marshall Training</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Heli Marshalling is a critical skill for ensuring safe helicopter operations in mountainous terrain. This training has enabled our Sherpas to excel in their skills at efficiently guiding helicopters during takeoff, landing, and ground operations. Clear communication, precise signaling, and understanding rotor wash dynamics are essential components of effective heli marshaling. With this training, we are now further alert and prepared for air operations in the mountains.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Helicopter Safety Training</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Safety is paramount in high-altitude environments. Our Sherpas undergo rigorous helicopter safety training, covering the following aspects:</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Emergency Procedures:</strong> Responding swiftly to emergencies such as sudden weather changes, or medical evacuations.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Loading and Unloading:</strong> Safely loading and unloading cargo and passengers from helicopters.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Navigation and Communication:</strong> Navigating through challenging landscapes and communicating effectively with pilots.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Risk Mitigation:</strong> Identifying and minimizing risks associated with helicopter operations.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">As the Sherpas prepare to ascend these majestic peaks, their proficiency in heli marshaling and helicopter safety will be their armor. SST remains committed to equipping our team with the knowledge and skills necessary for a successful and secure expedition.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Stay tuned for updates on 2024 expeditions as our Sherpas venture into bold Himalayan adventures, guided by expertise, resilience, and a deep respect for the mountains.</p>', '<p><strong>Heli Marshall and Safety Training for Sherpas: Preparing for Spring Expeditions 2024</strong></p>', 'heli-marshall-and-safety-training-for-sherpas-preparing-for-spring-expeditions', '1709288291370328522', 5, 0, 0, 49, '1-tCoGimnnrLPZlPCynNfr9SSUK7ONSRVoa1rcWHYl.JPG', 'heli-marshal-training-vzfZpgOL6gs6MllwFzPdCQwAf7kPxW2xjg7I1yQX.jpg', NULL, 'Heli Marshall and Safety Training for Sherpas: Preparing for Spring Expeditions 2024', 'Heli Marshall and Safety Training for Sherpas: Preparing for Spring Expeditions 2024', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'en', '2024-03-01 10:18:11', '2024-03-05 08:01:34'),
(137, '2024-03-13', 1, 'single', 'single', 'EXPEDITION SEASON (SPRING – 2024) UPDATES', 'Spring 2024', '<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Kathmandu, March 13: Recently, SST has been offered the responsibility of Rope Fixing on Everest and Lhotse. Every year, a team of veteran climbers and Sherpas prepare the standard climbing route for the season&rsquo;s ascents. The responsibility of fixing routes on Everest and Lhotse is provided by the <strong><a href=\"https://eoanepal.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Expeditions Operators\' Association Nepal (EOA-Nepal)</a>.</strong> With our experienced and competent climber team, we look forward to maintaining a secure route to the top of the world.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">SST has also been entrusted with rope fixings on <strong><a href=\"https://www.sevensummittreks.com/page/mt-makalu-expedition-8485m.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Makalu</a></strong> and <strong><a href=\"https://www.sevensummittreks.com/page/mt-annapurna-i-expedition-8091m.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Annapurna</a></strong> mountains as well.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">To ensure the rope fixing is done before the onset of the climbing period, our first group of logistics team including the basecamp manager, has proceeded to Everest already. The team, currently at Basecamp, shall build SST&rsquo;s basecamp site as well as prepare all resources to fix ropes to set up the climbing route.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The home to Shishapangma, the north and east faces of Everest as well as the standard climbing face of Cho Oyu, SST has also been facilitating VISA and administrative processes for expeditions in Tibet, China. As Tibet is a land of restricted access, acquiring permits and transporting logistics is a tough thing that not many agencies can pull off. However, SST has managed a special request with the Tibetan authorities to ensure our expeditions operate in Tibet without any issues.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">So far this season, SST has confirmed bookings of 65 climbers for Everest which is the leading figure in the Nepali adventure industry. SST is all set to organize expeditions in all 8000ers of Nepal (<strong><a href=\"https://www.sevensummittreks.com/page/mt-everest-expedition-884886m-south.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Everest</a></strong>,<strong> <a href=\"https://www.sevensummittreks.com/page/mt-kangchenjunga-expedition-8586m.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Kanchenjunga</a></strong>,<strong> <a href=\"https://www.sevensummittreks.com/page/mt-lhotse-expedition-8516m.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Lhotse</a></strong>,<strong> <a href=\"https://www.sevensummittreks.com/page/mt-makalu-expedition-8485m.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Makalu</a></strong>,<strong> <a href=\"https://www.sevensummittreks.com/page/mt-dhaulagiri-expedition-8167m.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Dhaulagiri</a></strong>,<strong> <a href=\"https://www.sevensummittreks.com/page/mt-annapurna-i-expedition-8091m.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Annapurna</a></strong>) and Tibet except Manaslu which is an autumn climb.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">For a smooth operation of all expeditions in all regions, we have completed preparations in Kathmandu. Our team has meticulously planned everything that&rsquo;s needed for a safe and fulfilling mountaineering expedition &ndash; guides, Sherpas, support staff, logistics, technical gear and equipment, high-altitude foods, campsite management plans, and transportation systems. This ensures our commitment to safety and fulfillment of the climber&rsquo;s expectation of a Himalayan climb.<img src=\"http://www.sevensummittreks.com/storage/photos/1/General/Blog.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1077\" height=\"720\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">SST, in collaboration with Heli Everest Pvt. Ltd., recently organized a comprehensive Heli Marshall and Safety Training for our Sherpa team. This training, scheduled just before the Spring Expeditions 2024, aims to enhance the skills and preparedness of our Sherpas who will be venturing into the high mountains. Similarly, our climbing staff were also given First Aid and Mountaineering Refreshment Training. Our climbing team is thus, prepared and excited to kick off the season.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">SST&rsquo;s Karakoram expeditions are well in the process of acquiring permits, managing logistics, and ensuring the best services to offer to our valued climbers.</p>', '<p><strong>Seven Summit Treks is excited to share our newest updates regarding the spring season of 2024.</strong></p>', 'expedition-season-spring-2024-updates', '1710321773621511822', 5, 0, 0, 50, 'blog-2024-cn6ARoXwcviWS7bMncv7IBBiozk1TEM6e58Jzryy.jpg', 'blog-2024-9KLvI1URXEISIDOhSFmUg8yJ5zmPZyq8xCF7Rw6c.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'en', '2024-03-13 09:22:53', '2024-03-13 14:05:12'),
