(139, '2024-04-28', 1, 'single', 'single', 'Everest route opens to Camp IV', 'Everest route opens to Camp IV', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Kathmandu, April 28: A team of 11 Sherpas from Seven Summit Treks (SST), a leading trekking and expedition company based in Kathmandu, completed fixing the rope lines at South Col (Camp IV 7950m) this afternoon, said SST.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Accordingly, the route to Camp IV of Mt. Everest and Lhotse has been opened for all climbers for rotation and acclimatization hikes this season. More than 390 permits for Everest and over 130 permits for Lhotse have been issued to date, according to available data from the authority of Nepal. Earlier this spring season, Seven Summit Treks successfully opened the summit routes on Makalu and Annapurna I.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Seven Summit Treks had been entrusted with the task of rope fixing on the mountains by the Expeditions Operators\' Association Nepal (EOA-Nepal).</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Rope fixing team on Everest and Lhotse include Mingma Dendi Sherpa, Tenzing Gyalje Sherpa, Namgel Dorjee Tamang, Pemba Tashi Sherpa, Gelje Sherpa, Dawa Sherpa, Phurba Chhotar Sherpa, Suku Bahadur Tamang, Lakpa Rinjin Sherpa, Tashi Sherpa and Pam Dorjee Sherpa.</p>', '<p>Everest route opens to Camp IV</p>', 'everest-route-opens-to-camp-iv', '1714325987318730238', 5, 0, 0, 51, 'camp-iv-everest-IK1lCD0DI9rKpQ61mWG9ejpfyYl9NEKB5DpWbVUU.jpg', 'camp-iv-everest-qk2SBCCRymGqDo5tqxiaNgdVkv1mDvhbyf1Qcsuf.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Everest route opens to Camp IV</p>', NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'en', '2024-04-28 17:39:47', '2024-04-30 03:16:31'),
(140, '2024-04-29', 1, 'single', 'single', 'Mountaineering Degree students embark on Gyaji Kang (7038 m) Expedition', 'Mountaineering Degree students embark on Gyaji Kang (7038 m) Expedition', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Kathmandu, April 29: A team of 29 students from the Nepal Mountain Academy (NMA) is aiming to climb Gyaji Kang as part of their academic degree. Led mountaineering instructor/IFMGA certified guides; Pasang Kaji Sherpa (Chief instructor), Gelje Sherpa and Jamling Bhote, and under the supervision of field supervisor Shiva Prasad Jaishi, also the campus chief, the expedition team has departed to complete the \'Gyaji Kang (7038m) Research Expedition-2024\' this morning, said NMA, adding that the climb is part of the curriculum for Bachelor of Mountaineering Studies (BMS) programme.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Seven Summit Treks, a leading Kathmandu-based trekking and expedition company, has provided supports, equipping the climbing team with climbing guides and support crew, and managing expedition logistics, ensuring their safety and comfort throughout the journey. The mountain attempt marks the third academic mountaineering research expedition above 7000m organised by the college, showcasing its commitment to experiential learning and exploration, said NMA.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Meanwhile, on an occasion, NMA bade farewell to the climbing students, and other team members, offering its best wishes to them. \"We send our heartfelt best wishes to the entire team as they embark on this great adventure. May your journey be filled with excitement, learning, and above all, safety.\"&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Located in the northern part of Manang in Nepal on the Nepal-China border, Gyaji Kang is a popular climb. Not much as its neighbouring peak Himlung but Gyaji Kang offers climbers an exciting and challenging 7000er experience. Climbers take upon the expedition to this mountain as a prepatory climb for 8000er or more challenging climbs. The location and approach via the hidden Nar-Phu valley makes the trek to this mountain a journey of a lifetime. Similarly, trekkers can enjoy a variety of landscapes from the subtropical lowlands to the hidden Himalayan valleys and Tibetan plateau behind the mighty Himalayan range is a wonder. Sightings of the mighty Annpurna, Dhaulagiri mountains and the elusive Snow Leopard are among the biggest highlights of the expedition.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The mountain was accessible for climbing expeditions only after 2002, making it least explored, and presents climbing difficulties due to challenges posed by factors, including potential avalanches, and extreme cold. However, Hyaji Kang is a hidden gem of the central western Himalaya.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We wish the expedition team the very best.</p>', '<p>Mountaineering Degree students embark on Gyaji Kang (7038 m) Expedition</p>', 'mountaineering-degree-students-embark-on-gyaji-kang-7038-m-expedition', '1714447063912429026', 5, 0, 0, 52, 'nma-banner-zVJBeRB1tIY5rdNkOPOEztmUHVbIhjeycUDHFAxT.jpg', 'nma-banner-qCYP0X9uWnjUaUIIFGmyAQI05vJNsz0eAqaXLMo4.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Mountaineering Degree students embark on Gyaji Kang (7038 m) Expedition</p>', NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'en', '2024-04-30 03:17:43', '2024-04-30 03:24:00'),
(141, '2024-05-06', 1, 'single', 'single', 'A team of 13  mountaineers climbs Makalu this afternoon', 'A team of 13 mountaineers climbs Makalu this afternoon', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Kathmandu, May 6: A team of 12 climbers, including Sherpas, scaled Mount Makalu this afternoon. The climbing team stood atop the fifth highest mountain on earth (8,485m) at around 3 pm with Seven Summit Treks (SST), a leading Kathmandu-based expedition operator, said SST.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The expedition was part of the SST Makalu Expedition 2024.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&ldquo;Summit. Hardest summit of my life and not easy to come down. So epic, so exhausted, so exposed. Made the summit around 3, heading down now. So tired,&rdquo; said Australian mountaineer Allie Pepper following her successful ascent of the peak. She made it to the top of the mountain without supplemental oxygen.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>The summiteers :&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Shima Afsari (Iran)</li>\r\n<li>Graciela Flor Cuenca Blas (Peru) (No O2)</li>\r\n<li>Ahmad Mohammad Mousa Bani-Hani (Jordan)</li>\r\n<li>Afsaneh Hesami Fard (Iran)</li>\r\n<li>Alessandra Kate Pepper (Australia) (No O2)</li>\r\n<li>Tashi Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n<li>Pema Rinje Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n<li>Lakpa Tenji Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n<li>Phurba Dorchi Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n<li>Mingtemba Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n<li>Ngima Wangdak Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n<li>Tawa Chhiri Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n<li>Yangji Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n</ol>', '<p><strong>A team of 13 mountaineers climbs Makalu this afternoon </strong></p>', 'a-team-of-13-mountaineers-climbs-makalu-this-afternoon', '1715054787160244700', 5, 0, 0, 53, 'maka-banner-flECLgUNwXvBQ6y9G6kfNOTXVg8hU44YFD8k16k8.jpg', 'maka-thumbnail-n4AKUVgIOZMBvE3zm0hnq2G4PFf00v5sTwDZHx7o.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><strong>A team of 13 mountaineers climbs Makalu this afternoon </strong></p>', NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'en', '2024-05-07 04:06:27', '2024-05-09 04:10:36'),
(142, '2024-05-06', 1, 'single', 'single', 'Seven Summit Treks’ fixing team summits Lhotse', 'Seven Summit Treks’ fixing team summits Lhotse', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Kathmandu, May 6: Mount Lhotse, the world\'s fourth-highest peak (8,516m), is now open for expeditions for this spring 2024 season.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;A team of 7 Sherpas climbed the peak today, opening a route to the summit. The fixing team from Seven Summit Treks (SST), a leading expedition operator based in Kathmandu, reached the top of the mountain at 9:30 pm (Nepal time), said SST General Manager Thaneswar Guragai.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The team successfully fixed ropes to the top of the peak under the Expedition Operators\' Association Nepal (EOA-Nepal), he added. \"With this summit bid starts, our team is all well at the Base Camp, and is eager to push for the summit now.\"</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The SST Lhotse fixing team comprised:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Dendi Sherpa (Mali-8, Dolakha)</li>\r\n<li>Tenjing Gyalje Sherpa (Khumbu Pasang Lhamu-4, Solukhumbu)</li>\r\n<li>Namgel Dorjee Tamang (Khumjung-7, Solukhumbu)</li>\r\n<li>Pemba Tashi Sherpa (Makalu-9, Sankhuwasabha)</li>\r\n<li>Dawa Sherpa (Makalu-8, Sankhuwasabha)</li>\r\n<li>Tashi Sherpa (Sisuwakhola-9, Sankhuwasabha)</li>\r\n<li>Pam Dorjee Sherpa (Juving-1, Solukhumbu)</li>\r\n</ol>', '<p><strong>Seven Summit Treks&rsquo; fixing team summits Lhotse</strong></p>', 'seven-summit-treks-fixing-team-summits-lhotse', '1715054914240179405', 5, 0, 0, 54, 'lhotse-banner-zTAFsZ2qRrhplZHtDICtdfsRcNJWMu7l9AofLMiG.jpg', 'lhotse-thumbnail-vLWdvyJILEAVpzbyqG0Q6f10XTFndT1dIxYHxDBU.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><strong>Seven Summit Treks&rsquo; fixing team summits Lhotse</strong></p>', NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'en', '2024-05-07 04:08:34', '2024-05-12 06:57:50'),
(143, '2024-05-10', 1, 'single', 'single', 'Seven Summit Treks’ fixing team summit Mt. Everest, Summit route opens for climbers', 'Seven Summit Treks’ fixing team summit Mt. Everest, Summit route opens for climbers', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Kathmandu, 10 May: Mt Everest (8848.86m), the world\'s highest peak is now open for expeditions for this spring 2024 season.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A team of 10 Sherpas climbed the peak today, opening a route to the summit. The fixing team from Seven Summit Treks (SST), a leading expedition operator based in Kathmandu, reached the top of the mountain at 8:15 pm (Nepal time), said SST General Manager Thaneswar Guragai.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The team successfully fixed ropes to the top of the peak under the Expedition Operators\' Association Nepal (EOA-Nepal), he added. \"With this summit bid starts, our team is all well at the Base Camp, and is eager to push for the summit now.\"</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The SST Everest fixing team comprised:</p>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Dendi Sherpa (Mali-8, Dolakha)</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Tenjing Gyalje Sherpa (Khumbu Pasang Lhamu-4, Solukhumbu)</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Namgel Dorjee Tamang (Khumjung-7, Solukhumbu)</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Suku Bahadur Tamang (Makalu-1, Sankhuwasabha)</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Dawa Rinje Sherpa (Makalu-5, Sankhuwasabha)</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Dawa Sherpa (Makalu-8, Sankhuwasabha)</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Lakpa Rinjin Sherpa (Makalu-3, Sankhuwasabha)</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Pemba Tashi Sherpa (Makalu-9, Sankhuwasabha)</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Pam Dorjee Sherpa (Juving-1, Solukhumbu)</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Lakpa Thinduk Sherpa (Makalu-2, Sankhuwasabha)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Stay tuned for more updates as the summit season progresses on the majestic slopes of Mt. Everest.</p>', '<p>Seven Summit Treks&rsquo; fixing team summit Mt. Everest, Summit route opens for climbers</p>', 'seven-summit-treks-fixing-team-summit-mt-everest-summit-route-opens-for-climbers', '1715502966391672020', 5, 0, 0, 55, 'everest-banner-JX603AdaLX8QBYJIVbNUCQvG0nHtM8rl0RG0uBnI.jpg', 'everest-thumbnail-TowNmz0Qnb51eBISddFymAhcTWtDfdIY1JE8LvuD.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Seven Summit Treks&rsquo; fixing team summit Mt. Everest, Summit route opens for climbers</p>', NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'en', '2024-05-12 08:36:06', '2024-05-13 04:10:15'),
(145, '2024-05-22', 1, 'single', 'single', 'Kami Rita Sherpa climbs Mt. Everest for record 30th time', 'Kami Rita Sherpa climbs Mt. Everest for record 30th time', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Kathmandu, May 22: Veteran climber Kami Rita Sherpa scaled Sagarmatha for a staggering 30th time, beating his own record for the most ascent of the world&rsquo;s highest peak. Earlier this month, on May 12, he made his 29th ascent.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Kami Rita stood atop the mountain this morning at 7:49 am, confirmed Tashi Lakpa Sherpa, Managing Director of Seven Summit Treks (SST), a leading Kathmandu-based expedition operator.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This ascent earns him the title of &lsquo;Most Successful Ascent of Mt. Everest by an Individual.&rsquo;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The expedition was organized by SST, and he was leading a mountaineering expedition team comprising about 20 climbers.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Kami Rita, 54, originally from Thame village in Solukhumbu, Nepal, who works as Senior Guide at SST, has dedicated his life to mountaineering being passionate about Mt Everest in particular with his 29th successful summit. Born on January 17, 1970, he developed a deep passion for climbing from a young age and has been in the field of mountaineering for over two decades.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">His mountaineering journey began in 1992 when he joined an expedition to Everest as a support staff member. His father was his inspiration. In 1950, when Nepal opened its borders to climbers from abroad, his father became one of the earliest professional guides for expeditions. Although his father&rsquo;s climbing career was cut short in 1992 after he suffered severe frostbite, Kami Rita\'s journey began that same year as a cook&rsquo;s assistant at Everest&rsquo;s base camp. He had reportedly been hauling gear as a porter since the age of 12. Kami Rita&rsquo;s journey to Everest began in 1994 when he joined an expedition and climbed successfully as a climbing Sherpa.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Since then, Kami Rita has fearlessly embarked on numerous expeditions, summiting Everest multiple times. Kami Rita&rsquo;s achievements extend beyond Everest, having also conquered other formidable peaks, including K2, Cho Oyu, Lhotse, and Manaslu.</p>', '<p>Kami Rita Sherpa climbs Mt. Everest for record 30th time</p>', 'kami-rita-sherpa-climbs-mt-everest-for-record-30th-time', '1716363265986666233', 5, 0, 0, 56, 'kami-rita-banner-iCIPAyCWWdPA9EhqSNci1VrHgnJqDYThY4KNCltA.jpg', 'kami-rita-thumbnail-sjfKJ1SVbmsv1YdotTZOJrJ97nXOJoZTsKjwjFjF.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Kami Rita Sherpa climbs Mt. Everest for record 30th time</p>', NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'en', '2024-05-22 07:34:25', '2024-05-22 08:49:47'),
(146, '2024-05-22', 1, 'single', 'single', 'Seven Summit Treks\' Guide Dawa Finjok climbs Everest for record three times in 8 days', 'Seven Summit Treks\' Guide Dawa Finjok climbs Everest for record three times in 8 days', '<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\"><strong>Kathmandu, May 22:</strong> Nepal\'s climber Dawa Finjok Sherpa has made history by summiting Mt Everest in eight days. He achieved this remarkable feat in 8 days, 13 hours, and 35 minutes, setting a record for the most Everest ascents within a short time.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\">He stood atop the world\'s highest peak (8848.86m) on May 20 at 9 pm, said Chhang Dawa Sherpa, Director of Seven Summit Treks, a leading Kathmandu-based expedition operator.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\">Dawa made his first ascent on May 12, 2024 at 7:25 am, followed by his second summit on May 17, 2024 at 3:16 pm. He achieved all these three ascents with supplemental oxygen as part of the Seven Summit Treks Everest Expedition.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\">He is aiming to attempt the peak four times within a short period, embarking on this mission in a few days, it has been reported.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\">His passion and accomplishment represents dedication, hardship, and physical and mental strength of the entire Sherpa community, said SST. \"His feat is not just a personal triumph, but a source of inspiration for the entire mountaineering community.\"</p>', '<p><strong>Seven Summit Treks\' Guide Dawa Finjok climbs Everest for record three times in 8 days&nbsp;</strong></p>', 'seven-summit-treks-guide-dawa-finjok-climbs-everest-for-record-three-times-in-8-days', '1716365351251366724', 5, 0, 0, 57, 'dawa-finjok-FU8BNha1vsIlMvJoH6ipSsXtB0lN7X3isviWKcsA.jpg', 'dawa-finjok-NUPzCpONtKBFIKoCyyjj68ifQNZ8BPNdyrpA0fJM.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><strong>Seven Summit Treks\' Guide Dawa Finjok climbs Everest for record three times in 8 days&nbsp;</strong></p>', NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'en', '2024-05-22 08:09:11', '2024-05-22 08:29:13'),
(147, '2024-05-24', 1, 'single', 'single', 'Polish climber Krzyzowski sets record-making double header summit of Lhotse and Everest without Supplement O2', 'Polish climber Krzyzowski sets record-making double header summit of Lhotse and Everest without Supplement O2', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Kathmandu, May 24: Polish climber Piotr Jerzy Krzyzowski has made history by becoming the first and fastest person to climb both Lhotse and Everest without supplemental oxygen. This historic achievement was made in 1 day, 23 hours and 22 minutes.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Krzyzewski reached the summit of Lhotse, the fourth-highest mountain in the world (8,516m) on May 21 at 2:38 pm, said Thaneswar Guragai, General Manager of Seven Summit Treks, a leading Kathmandu-based expedition operator. Just two days later, he made another historic achievement, summiting Mt Everest, the world\'s highest peak, soaring to 8,848.86m above sea level on May 23 at 2:00 pm.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">He achieved this feat as part of the SST Everest-Lhotse Expedition.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Krzyzowski&rsquo;s achievement took place under extraordinary conditions, making the summits a record. He ascended both peaks without supplemental oxygen, without Sherpa assistance, and without descending to Camp 2 or Base Camp between the summits, highlighting a new pinnacle of minimalist, and self-reliant alpinism, said Guragai.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">His journey began with the ascent of Lhotse, reaching the summit on May 21 and marking the halfway point of his ambitious plan for a record. On May 23, Krzyzowski&rsquo;s perseverance culminated in reaching Everest&rsquo;s summit at 2:00 pm.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Achieving two higher 8000ers without supplemental oxygen and support underscores the remarkable accomplishment, showcasing an extraordinary level of determination, he said.</p>', '<p><strong>Polish climber Krzyzowski sets record-making double header summit of Lhotse and Everest without Supplement O2</strong></p>', 'polish-climber-krzyzowski-sets-recordmaking-double-header-summit-of-lhotse-and-everest-without-supplement-o2', '1716701636142733011', 5, 0, 0, 58, 'piotr-banner-BkWe7IUhy1eVLNzEHJixMlciW7ZlnlTOncQNG6i8.jpg', 'piotr-thumbnai-KyKJzFSOou1SILQsfJRhvY617szDi8IDStxGWVPT.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><strong>Polish climber Krzyzowski sets record-making double header summit of Lhotse and Everest without Supplement O2</strong></p>', NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'en', '2024-05-26 05:33:56', '2024-05-26 06:08:44');
