(148, '2024-06-07', 1, 'single', 'single', 'HISTORIC ACHIEVEMENT ON CHO OYU (8188M) NEPAL SIDE (SST- NEPAL ROUTE)', NULL, '<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\"><strong>HISTORIC ACHIEVEMENT ON CHO OYU (8188M) NEPAL SIDE (SST- NEPAL ROUTE)</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\">June 7: French climber Alasdair McKenzie, alongside a team of veteran Nepalese Sherpas, has made history by achieving the summit of Cho Oyu on 7 June, 2024, via the formidable Nepal side.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\">Alasdair McKenzie, partnering in his climb with Gelje, Tenging Gyaljen and other Sherpas, stood atop the world\'s sixth-highest mountain at a height of 8,188 meters above sea level at 8:35 PM (Nepal Time) via the S-SW Ridge (SST-Nepal Route), said Mingma Sherpa, who is handling the entire expedition movement from the basecamp of Cho Oyu.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\"> “McKenzie, Tenging Gyaljen, Gelje and some others Sherpas reached the summit. The team started at 2 AM (approx.) from Camp IV, and after a continuous effort of over 17 hours, they made it to the top” – Mingma Sherpa, Chairman of SST added.  This remarkable achievement was the result of a meticulously planned expedition that started in March and commenced in the first week of May from Lukla.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\">Despite being summited for the first time in 1954 by Dr. Herbert Tichy, Sepp Joechler, and Pasang Dawa Sherpa, the standard climbing route lies in Tibet. Cho Oyu\'s Nepal side is known for its steep, vertical walls rising thousands of meters, making it one of the greatest present time challenges. The face of the mountain from the Nepal side had not witnessed a successful climb since 2009 (by Denis Urubko and Boris Dedeshko – Route: South Face), despite numerous attempts, highlighting the difficulty involved.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\">The expedition faced numerous challenges along the way. By May 30, McKenzie and the Sherpa team, including Mingteamba Sherpa, had fixed ropes up to 7625m but were forced to return to the base camp due to a shortage of ropes. On June 4, with all preparations in place, the team set off on their final summit push from the base camp.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\"><strong>The successful summit has accomplished by our victorious team:</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Alasdair McKenzie (France) (Leader) – Completed his 13th 8000er.</li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Gelje Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Chhangba Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Tenging Gyaljen Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Lakpa Temba Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Lakpa Tenji Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ngima Ongda Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\">The team\'s dedication and hard work, along with the exceptional logistics and management provided by Seven Summit Treks were crucial in overcoming the formidable challenges posed by Cho Oyu’s Nepal side. The Sherpas, the team members, the leader, and the climbing strategy deserve commendable praise for this achievement.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"http://www.sevensummittreks.com/storage/photos/1/8000m/Mckenzie with Permit.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"832\" height=\"679\"></p>\r\n<div class=\"flex-shrink-0 flex flex-col relative items-end\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"pt-0.5 juice:pt-0\">\r\n<div class=\"gizmo-bot-avatar flex h-6 w-6 items-center justify-center overflow-hidden rounded-full juice:h-8 juice:w-8\">\r\n<div class=\"relative p-1 rounded-sm flex items-center justify-center bg-token-main-surface-primary text-token-text-primary h-8 w-8\" style=\"text-align: right;\"><em>(Left): Alasdair receiving the official permit to climb Cho Oyu from the Nepal side from the Director of the Department of Tourism, Rakesh Gurung (Right).</em></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\"><strong>Expedition ground handling and leadership by Mingma Sherpa (Chairman of SST) </strong><br>This expedition was also executed under the careful preparation and supervision of Mingma Sherpa, Chairman of SST, which is a phenomenal factor that led to this historic achievement mountaineering achievement and logistical expertise, drawing from a wealth of experience in arranging successful ascents on the world\'s highest peaks. As the first South Asian to climb all 14 mountains above 8,000 meters, Mingma\'s unparalleled mastery of high-altitude logistics, climbing strategy, and profound understanding of mountains is second to none.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\"><strong>A New Era in Nepali Mountaineering</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\">This historic ascent not only marks a significant milestone in the mountaineering world but also opens up new opportunities for climbers from Nepal as well as around the globe aspiring to climb from the Nepalese side. With this success, Cho Oyu is now more accessible from Nepal, heralding a new era in the Nepali mountaineering, and inspiring future expeditions to tackle its challenging routes.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\">Seven Summit Treks, the organiser of this expedition, takes immense pride in this achievement, and extends gratitude to all the climbers, past and present, who have contributed to this historic moment.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\">Massive congratulations team and we wish you a safe descent and hope to warmly receive you back here.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\"><em>Stay Connected !</em></p>', '<p>HISTORIC ACHIEVEMENT ON CHO OYU (8188M) NEPAL SIDE (SST- NEPAL ROUTE)</p>', 'historic-achievement-on-cho-oyu-8188m-nepal-side-sst-nepal-route', '1717775245369370952', 5, 0, 0, 59, 'high-camp-cho-oyu-aTNGX684M2swV3kO5p3b7nljnOLbHCu7nbHU68Pq.jpg', 'cho-oyu-with-sherpa-vRSpP0c6TMSiGrUP99e0qHE8be9Tklzqa2S26jhX.jpeg', NULL, 'Cho oyu Nepal side, Nepal side Cho Oyu, Cho Oyu Climbing, last ascent of Cho Oyu.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'en', '2024-06-07 15:47:25', '2024-09-10 05:27:13'),
(149, '2024-07-10', 1, 'single', 'single', '9 mountaineers climb Nanga Parbat', '9 mountaineers climb Nanga Parbat', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Kathmandu, July 10: 9 mountaineers, including Sherpas, scaled Nanga Parbat on July 10, 2024. This achievement follows a group of 4 climbers, who climbed the mountain on July 9 fixing the route for this season.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Two of the climbers--Israfil Ashurli (Azerbaijan) and Vadim Pirmin Druelle (France)--achieved a summit without the use of supplemental oxygen.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The rope fixing team made it to the top at 17:45 local time, said Thaneswar Guragai, General Manager of Seven Summit Treks, a leading Nepal-based expedition operator, and the expedition organizer.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>The following climbers summited the mountain on July 10: </strong></p>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>Al Harthy Nadhira Ahmed Abdullah (Oman)</li>\r\n<li>Vibeke Andrea Sefland (Norway)</li>\r\n<li>Thomas Ntavarinos (Greece)</li>\r\n<li>Israfil Ashurli (Azerbaijan) (No O2)</li>\r\n<li>Vadim Pirmin Druelle (France) (No O2)</li>\r\n<li>Pasang Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n<li>Ngima Wangdak Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n<li>Ngima Dorchi Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n<li>Phubadhile Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>The climbers who scaled the mountain on July 9 included: </strong></p>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>Lakpa Temba Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n<li>Pemba Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n<li>Dilawar Sadpara (Pakistan)</li>\r\n<li>Fida Ali (Pakistan)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Nanga Parbat </strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Located in Pakistan, Nanga Parbat is the ninth-highest mountain in the world and the second-highest in Pakistan. Standing at 8,125 meters above sea level, the mountain is known by various names including \"Nanga Parbat,\" (Naked Mountain) in Urdu, and \"Diamir,\" which means \"King of the Mountains.\"</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The mountain was first climbed on July 3, 1953, by Austrian climber Hermann Buhl. He did this solo ascent without supplemental oxygen. The mountain is known for its difficult and dangerous climbing routes with a high fatality rate, earning it the nickname \"Killer Mountain.\"</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The peak has been the focus of numerous expeditions and climbing attempts, with varying degrees of success. Despite its challenges, it continues attracting climbers worldwide who seek to climb on its formidable slopes. The mountain\'s breathtaking beauty and formidable nature make it a prominent feature in high-altitude mountaineering.</p>', '<p><strong>9 mountaineers climb Nanga Parbat </strong></p>', '9-mountaineers-climb-nanga-parbat', '1720603726376522538', 5, 0, 0, 60, 'nanga-banner-IBdJ3VXLzWjAikN3SiFBKbcDA9TGblJQwVJiiIOu.jpg', 'nanga-thumbnail-IRos5OMxYxfkzyWcGRc0EEBYKFmYlCV8COGwx8wV.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><strong>9 mountaineers climb Nanga Parbat </strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'en', '2024-07-10 09:28:46', '2024-07-14 05:02:49'),
(150, '2024-07-23', 1, 'single', 'single', 'Seven Summit Treks Team Conquers Gasherbrum II', 'Seven Summit Treks Team Conquers Gasherbrum II', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We are excited to announce the successful ascent of Gasherbrum II by our incredible Seven Summit Treks team members and Sherpas on different dates! This monumental achievement is a testament to their extraordinary perseverance, strength, and teamwork.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This remarkable feat wouldn\'t have been possible without the hard work and unwavering spirit of each team member. Their dedication and resilience have culminated in this extraordinary success, showcasing the true essence of mountaineering excellence.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Summiteer List (21 July 2024):</strong></p>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>Alina Pekova (Russia)</li>\r\n<li>Dorota Lidia Rasinska-Samocko (Poland)</li>\r\n<li>Josette Valloton (Switzerland)</li>\r\n<li>Marco Camandona (Italy)</li>\r\n<li>Shahida Jamil Afridi (Pakistan)</li>\r\n<li>Rana Hassan Javaid (Pakistan)</li>\r\n<li>Pasang Tenje Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n<li>Dawa Nurbu Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n<li>Chhangba Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n<li>Phurbu Kusang Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n<li>Pasang Dukpa Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Summiteer List (22 July 2024):</strong></p>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>Al Harthy Nadhira Ahmed Abdullah (Oman)</li>\r\n<li>Vadim Pirmin Druelle (France) - No O2</li>\r\n<li>Pasang Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Summiteer List (23 July 2024):</strong></p>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>Israfil Ashurli (Azerbaijan)</li>\r\n<li>Taraman Tamang (Nepal)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Seven Summit Treks achieved 100% summit success on Gasherbrum I this summer 2024.</strong></p>', '<p><strong>Seven Summit Treks Team Conquers Gasherbrum II</strong></p>', 'seven-summit-treks-team-conquers-gasherbrum-ii', '1721547473396438055', 5, 0, 0, 61, 'himlung-bannner-r8u8YQSQWJctvwuIhy4J00PiaJsa8uB5bxfKpvW1.jpg', 'g2-thumbnail-RErkzmo8sH6mTCiRrKNeeFmCovjK0qN0VAROkPZj.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><strong>Seven Summit Treks Team Conquers Gasherbrum II</strong></p>', NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'en', '2024-07-21 07:37:53', '2024-07-31 05:21:50'),
(151, '2024-07-28', 1, 'single', NULL, 'Seven Summit Treks Team Conquers Gasherbrum I', 'Seven Summit Treks Team Conquers Gasherbrum I', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">On July 28, 2024, the Seven Summit Treks team members and Sherpa guides achieved a remarkable feat&mdash;reaching the summit of Mt. Gasherbrum 1. Known for its challenging conditions and technical demands, this ascent marks a significant milestone in their climbing journey and a testament to their dedication and expertise.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The successful summit was the culmination of weeks of grueling acclimatization and strategic planning. The ascent was marked by careful attention to safety and environmental considerations, reflecting Seven Summit Treks&rsquo; commitment to sustainable mountaineering practices.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Summiteer List:</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Josette Valloton (Switzerland)</li>\r\n<li>Dorota Lidia Rasinska-Samocko (Poland)</li>\r\n<li>Marco Camandona (Italy) - No O2</li>\r\n<li>Dante Luboz (Italy) - No O2</li>\r\n<li>Vadim Pirmin Druelle (France) - No O2</li>\r\n<li>Chhangba Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n<li>Pasang Dukpa Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n<li>Pasang Tenje Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n</ol>', '<p>Seven Summit Treks Team Conquers Gasherbrum I</p>', 'seven-summit-treks-team-conquers-gasherbrum-i', '1722403858362760482', 5, 0, 0, 62, 'dhau-banner-yeyisMA2C2qlxWYJJ60zqCtlLGbW0BoFLO5trtpS.jpg', 'g1-thumbnail-3NpyLzJ23twCotWCeFCXX5D9ro6fQvOB9e8UzqZT.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Seven Summit Treks Team Conquers Gasherbrum I</p>', NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'en', '2024-07-31 05:30:58', '2024-07-31 05:30:58'),
(152, '2024-07-29', 1, 'single', NULL, 'Seven Summit Treks Achieves Grand Success on K2 (8611m)', 'Seven Summit Treks Achieves Grand Success on K2 (8611m)', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In a remarkable display of teamwork, Seven Summit Treks team members and Sherpa guides have achieved a significant milestone on K2, the world\'s second-highest peak.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The success of K2 is a testament to the comprehensive preparation and unwavering resolve of the Seven Summit Treks team. Our approach, which emphasizes safety, careful acclimatization, and respectful stewardship of the mountains, has set a new benchmark for high-altitude expeditions.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This achievement is particularly noteworthy given the peak&rsquo;s notorious reputation. K2, often dubbed the \"Savage Mountain,\" is known for its severe weather, steep slopes, and technical demands. Conquering it is no small feat, and Seven Summit Treks\' success reflects their commitment to pushing the boundaries of what is possible while maintaining the highest standards of safety and respect for the mountain.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Summiteer List (28 July 2024):</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Valeriy Babanov (Canada)</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Jorge Egocheaga Rodriguez (Spain)</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Ngo Hai Son (Vietnam)</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Naoko Watanabe (Japan)</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Mingtemba Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Mingma Nurbu Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Nurbu Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Phurba Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong>Summiteer List (29 July 2024):</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Paula Birgitta Strengell (Finland)</li>\r\n<li>Yuri Kruglov (Russia)</li>\r\n<li>Mahmoud Hashemisougheh (Iran)</li>\r\n<li>Farnaz Dyanatmoghadam (Iran)</li>\r\n<li>Saeid Mirzaei (Iran) - No O2</li>\r\n<li>Alessandra Kate Pepper (Australia)</li>\r\n<li>Chhepal Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n<li>Dawa Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n<li>Mingtemba Sherpa (Nepal)</li>\r\n<li>Ali Hassan (Pakistan)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Congratulations to the entire team at Seven Summit Treks for this monumental achievement.</p>', '<p><strong>Seven Summit Treks Achieves Grand Success on K2 (8611m)</strong></p>', 'seven-summit-treks-achieves-grand-success-on-k2-8611m', '1722410266843970683', 5, 0, 0, 63, 'k2-banner-jJNTys73thXcGRpo3lKkHpw7EdaY2B3pLK1UaRyR.jpg', 'k2-xH1FvFN0QNNrynFK4OtMrBF4x8WmGoXRgnhxzUC5.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><strong>Seven Summit Treks Achieves Grand Success on K2 (8611m)</strong></p>', NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'en', '2024-07-31 07:17:46', '2024-07-31 07:17:46');
