rong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em>The company will not be held responsible for any errors or modifications made to the account above number during the fund transfer process. </em></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em>Clients are responsible for all transfer fees incurred.</em></li>\r\n</ul>', '1', '2022-02-15 10:23:15', '2024-08-27 05:51:52'),
(34, '1', 'Cancellation', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We understand that circumstances can change, and it may become necessary to cancel a booked trip. To effectively manage operational costs associated with personnel and resources allocated to each trip, we have implemented the following cancellation policy. Please carefully review the terms outlined below:</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Cancellation Fees</strong><strong>:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>2(a) Cancellation 45 Days Before Departure:</strong> If you decide to cancel your trip 45 days or more before the scheduled departure from your country, the following terms will apply:</p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>The company will charge a cancellation fee of 30% of the total trip amount.</li>\r\n<li>The remaining amount will be refunded to you after deducting the processing charge of Nepal Rastra Bank.</li>\r\n<li><u>Alternatively, if you prefer, the refundable amount can be retained by the company as a charge for your future trip with Seven Summit Treks.</u></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>2(b) Cancellation 25 Days Before Departure:</strong> If you decide to cancel your trip between 25 days and 44 days before the scheduled departure from your country, the following terms will apply:</p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>The company will charge a cancellation fee ranging from 40% to 50% of the total trip amount.</li>\r\n<li>The remaining amount will be refunded to you as outlined in the terms of clause 2(a).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>2(c) Cancellation 1 Week Before Departure:</strong> If you decide to cancel your trip between 24 Days and the last week before the scheduled departure from your country, the following terms will apply:</p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>The company will charge a cancellation fee ranging from 60% to 70% of the total trip amount.</li>\r\n<li>The remaining amount will be refunded to you as outlined in the terms of clause 2(a).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>2(d) No Refund Once the Trip Begins:</strong> Once your trip has commenced (Started), there will be no refund available for any unused services or portions of the trip. You will be responsible for paying the full amount of the trip in this consequence.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Please Note:</strong><em> Cancellation fees are based on the total trip cost and reflect the expenses incurred in preparing for your journey. We strongly recommend purchasing comprehensive travel insurance to protect against unforeseen circumstances that may necessitate trip cancellation.</em></p>', '2', '2022-02-15 10:23:15', '2024-08-09 09:19:31'),
(35, '1', 'Late Booking', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Late booking can be done as early as 10 days before the departure from your country. But it is to be noted that it will involve additional cost.</p>', '3', '2022-02-15 10:23:15', '2022-04-04 08:02:14'),
(36, '1', 'Required Documentation', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Clients must submit a passport-sized photograph, and a copy of their passport, and complete the necessary forms. For the expedition above 8000m mountains, the client needs to provide a certificate verifying the successful summit of a peak exceeding 6,000 meters elevation upon trip confirmation. The company will not be held responsible for any issues arising from the client’s failure to submit the required documentation within the specified timeframe.</p>', '4', '2022-02-16 10:05:03', '2024-08-13 05:18:08'),
(37, '1', 'Insurance and Travel Risks', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Clients are required to purchase comprehensive travel insurance prior to departure, providing coverage for medical expenses, evacuation, and search and rescue missions. Given the inherent risks associated with trekking and expedition activities, particularly in high-altitude environments, we strongly recommend comprehensive insurance coverage for helicopter evacuations, trip cancellations, and personal accidents.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The company will collect client insurance information to facilitate necessary actions in the event of emergencies. In the case of a rescue, the company will coordinate with relevant rescue services and manage related paperwork. However, the company assumes no liability or financial responsibility for any losses or expenses not covered by the client’s insurance policy. Clients are solely responsible for all costs not covered by their insurance provider.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It is important to note that air evacuation options may be limited or unavailable in certain regions. Clients should be prepared for this possibility. While the company will provide support within the constraints of local regulations, the ultimate responsibility for client safety and well-being rests with the individual.</p>', '5', '2022-02-16 10:05:03', '2024-08-13 05:18:08'),
(38, '1', 'Incomplete Trips', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Clients will not be entitled to any compensation if they are unable to commence or complete the trek or expedition due to personal reasons, including but not limited to injury or illness. Additionally, in the event of a government-mandated permit revocation due to unforeseen circumstances such as natural disasters, the company will not be liable for any refunds or compensation.</p>', '6', '2022-02-16 10:05:03', '2024-08-09 09:19:31'),
(39, '1', 'Client Compliance and Authority', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Clients must agree to adhere to all local laws, regulations, and customs during their trip. The company bears no responsibility for clients engaging in any illegal activities. In the event of a client\'s unlawful conduct, the company reserves the right to contact local authorities. Any legal consequences arising from a client\'s actions are solely the client’s responsibility. The company is under no obligation to provide legal assistance or financial compensation in such circumstances.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The team leader or guide holds ultimate authority during the trek/expedition. These individuals are highly experienced and their decisions prioritize the safety and well-being of all participants. Clients agree to follow their instructions without exception. In the event of disputes or conflicts among clients, the company’s staff will mediate. If necessary, local authorities may be involved to resolve the matter.</p>', '7', '2022-02-16 10:05:03', '2024-08-13 05:18:08'),
(40, '1', 'Early Completion of ScheduleItinerary Modifications and Additional Costs', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Seven Summit Treks Pvt. Ltd. offers carefully designed standard packages based on extensive industry experience. We understand, however, that individual preferences may vary. Upon request, we can modify itineraries to accommodate specific client needs, provided that additional time and costs are agreed upon at the time of booking.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Circumstances beyond our control, such as adverse weather conditions or unforeseen events, may necessitate changes to the itinerary or pricing. In such cases, adjustments will be made in mutual agreement with the client.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Client-induced factors such as damage to company equipment, itinerary delays, requests for additional services beyond the original agreement, etc., are likely to increase the previously decided price.</p>', '8', '2022-02-17 04:20:50', '2024-08-09 09:19:31'),
(41, '1', 'Early Completion of Schedule', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Sometimes schedule may be completed a few days before the designated time, in such cases, no refund will be issued for the unused portion of the itinerary. For example, a 14-day trip concluded in 12 days will not result in a refund for the remaining 2 days.  As outlined in clause 2(d) of these terms, no refunds will be provided once a trip commences.</p>', '9', '2022-02-17 04:20:50', '2024-08-13 05:18:08'),
(42, '1', 'Early Trip Termination', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Clients who choose to prematurely end their trip due to personal emergencies or unforeseen circumstances will incur additional charges. These fees account for the logistical complexities involved in adjusting arrangements, including the return of porters and management of other operational requirements from the base camp. This process typically requires one to two days.</p>', '10', '2022-02-17 04:20:50', '2024-08-09 09:19:31'),
(43, '1', 'Flight Cancelations (International/ Domestic)', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In any flight cancellations, financial compensation will not be provided unless the cancellation is directly caused by the company’s actions. However, it is within the duty of the company to assist our clients by arranging hotel accommodations, subject to applicable charge.</p>', '11', '2022-02-17 04:20:50', '2024-08-13 05:18:08'),
(44, '1', 'Overnight Stay & Food', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In the event of an overnight stay necessitated by client circumstances, flight cancellations (domestic or international), or any other issues, clients will be responsible for associated accommodation and meal expenses. However, if the overnight stay is caused due to the company’s reason, the company will cover the costs of accommodations.</p>', '12', '2022-02-17 04:20:50', '2024-08-13 05:18:08'),
(45, '1', 'Agreement of Services', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Trekking and expedition destinations often present challenging conditions far removed from modern conveniences of the 21st century. In some instances, clients may not get exactly what they are looking for, even if they are willing to pay for it. As a hosting company, we try to provide the highest level of service. Unexpected events may occasionally arise where we are unable to meet specific expectations. We appreciate clients\' understanding and flexibility in adapting to such situations. Most importantly, clients must have a clear comprehension of the potential challenges and limitations associated with their chosen itinerary before booking.</p>', '13', '2022-02-17 04:20:50', '2024-08-09 09:40:25'),
(46, '1', 'Meals', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We have carefully selected the best available hotels, tea-houses, lodges, and experienced cooks for basecamp and in higher camps. However, the taste may differ from your usual preferences. We prioritize providing the best possible food options, but clients are expected to follow the guide\'s recommendations when selecting menu items.</p>', '14', '2022-02-17 04:20:50', '2024-08-09 09:19:31'),
(47, '1', 'Stuff and Equipment', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If Seven Summit Treks Pvt. Ltd. provides any materials, gear, or equipment, whether owned by the company or not, the client is obligated to return it to the company\'s designated representative upon completion of the trip, expedition, or trek. Any damage incurred to the equipment must be compensated for at a rate determined by the company.</p>', '15', '2022-02-17 04:20:50', '2024-08-09 09:19:31'),
(48, '1', 'Publicity', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Seven Summit Treks may request clients’ permission to use photographs and videos captured by clients, free of charge. Any materials provided will be used exclusively for marketing and promotional activities. Client privacy is paramount and will be strictly protected. We appreciate the clients’ cooperation in this matter.</p>', '16', '2022-02-17 04:20:50', '2024-08-13 05:18:08'),
(49, '1', 'Children', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">According to the Nepal Government’s Mountaineering Rules, individuals under the age of sixteen (16) are prohibited from climbing any mountain peak. While mountaineering is restricted for minors, trekking activities can be undertaken under the supervision of their legal guardians. All individuals below the age of sixteen (16) must be accompanied by a legal guardian for any trips.</p>', '17', '2022-02-17 04:20:50', '2024-08-13 05:18:08'),
(51, '2', 'Required Documentation', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Calibri Light\',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: major-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: major-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: major-latin;\">Clients must submit a passport-sized photograph, complete the necessary forms, and provide a certificate verifying the successful summit of a peak exceeding 7,000-meter elevation upon trip confirmation. The company will not be held responsible for any issues arising from the client’s failure to submit the required documentation within the specified timeframe.</span></p>', '4', '2022-02-20 08:44:43', '2024-08-16 07:40:34'),
(52, '2', 'Insurance and Travel Risks', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: major-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: major-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: major-latin;\">Clients are required to purchase comprehensive travel insurance prior to departure, providing coverage for medical expenses, evacuation, and search and rescue missions. Given the inherent risks associated with trekking and expedition activities, particularly in high-altitude environments, we strongly recommend comprehensive insurance coverage for helicopter evacuations, trip cancellations, and personal accidents.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: major-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: major-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: major-latin;\">The company will collect client insurance information to facilitate necessary actions in the event of emergencies. In the case of a rescue, the company will coordinate with relevant rescue services and manage related paperwork. However, the company assumes no liability or financial responsibility for any losses or expenses not covered by the client’s insurance policy. Clients are solely responsible for all costs not covered by their insurance provider.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin: 15.0pt 0in 15.0pt 0in;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: major-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: major-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: major-latin;\">It is important to note that air evacuation options may be limited or unavailable in certain regions. Clients should be prepared for this possibility. While the company will provide support within the constraints of local regulations, the ultimate responsibility for client safety and well-being rests with the individual.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin: 15.0pt 0in 15.0pt 0in;\"><u><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: \'Calibri Light\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #0d0d0d; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-themetint: 242;\">In most cases, the Pakistani army handles rescues, and the clients must pay the rescue charge beforehand. Later, the client can claim the amount from the insurance company.</span></u></p>', '5', '2022-02-20 08:53:42', '2024-08-16 07:40:34'),
(53, '2', 'Delay in Entry to Pakistan', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Calibri Light\',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: major-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: major-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: major-latin;\">Delays in entry to Pakistan due to unforeseen circumstances may occur. In the event of such delays preventing clients from entering the country as scheduled, any additional costs incurred due to an extended stay beyond the package duration will be the responsibility of the client. </span></p>', '6', '2022-02-20 08:53:42', '2024-08-16 07:40:34'),
(54, '2', 'Visa-Related Issues', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: \'Calibri Light\',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: major-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: major-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: major-latin;\">Visa approval is solely the responsibility of the client and is considered a personal matter. While we will provide assistance with visa procedures, we cannot guarantee visa issuance. The Pakistan government may deny a visa application based on nationality or other personal reasons. In such cases, Seven Summit Treks Pvt. Ltd. is not liable for visa denial. Refunds for the package will be processed in mutual agreement with the client, subject to applicable charges.</span></p>', '7', '2022-02-20 08:53:42', '2024-08-16 07:40:34'),
(55, '2', 'Incomplete Trips', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Calibri Light\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1;\">Clients will not be entitled to any compensation if they are unable to commence or complete the trek or expedition due to personal reasons, including but not limited to injury or illness. Additionally, in the event of a government-mandated permit revocation due to unforeseen circumstances such as natural disasters, the company will not be liable for any refunds or compensation.</span></p>', '8', '2022-02-20 08:53:42', '2024-08-16 07:40:34'),
(56, '2', 'Client Compliance and Authority', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Calibri Light\',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: major-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: major-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: major-latin;\">Clients must agree to adhere to all local laws, regulations, and customs during their trip. The company bears no responsibility for clients engaging in any illegal activities. In the event of a client\'s unlawful conduct, the company reserves the right to contact local authorities. Any legal consequences arising from a client\'s actions are solely the client’s responsibility. The company is under no obligation to provide legal assistance or financial compensation in such circumstances.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Calibri Light\',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: major-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: major-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: major-latin;\">The team leader or guide holds ultimate authority during the trek/expedition. These individuals are highly experienced and their decisions prioritize the safety and well-being of all participants. Clients agree to follow their instructions without exception. In the event of disputes or conflicts among clients, the company’s staff will mediate. If necessary, local authorities may be involved to resolve the matter.</span></p>', '9', '2022-02-20 08:53:42', '2024-08-16 07:40:34'),
(57, '2', 'Itinerary Modifications and Additional Costs', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: \'Calibri Light\',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: major-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: major-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: major-latin;\">Seven Summit Treks Pvt. Ltd. offers carefully designed standard packages based on extensive industry experience. We understand, however, that individual preferences may vary. Upon request, we can modify itineraries to accommodate specific client needs, provided that additional time and costs are agreed upon at the time of booking.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: \'Calibri Light\',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: major-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: major-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: major-latin;\">Circumstances beyond our control, such as adverse weather conditions or unforeseen events, may necessitate changes to the itinerary or pricing. In such cases, adjustments will be made in mutual agreement with the client.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: \'Calibri Light\',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: major-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: major-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: major-latin;\">Client-induced factors such as damage to company equipment, itinerary delays, requests for additional services beyond the original agreement, etc., are </span><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: \'Calibri Light\',sans-serif; color: #0d0d0d; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-themetint: 242;\">likely to increase the previously decided price.</span></p>', '10', '2022-02-20 08:53:42', '2024-08-16 07:40:34'),
