o 9)</li>\r\n<li>Kaike Rural Municipality (All areas of wards no. 1 to 7)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 33.3828%;\" width=\"208\">\r\n<p>USD 20 per person/ week</p>\r\n<p>USD 5 per person /day (beyond 1 week)</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 10.9792%; text-align: center;\" width=\"60\">\r\n<p>7.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 55.638%;\" width=\"356\">\r\n<p>Dolakha</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Gaurishankhar Rural Municipality (All areas of ward no. 9)</li>\r\n<li>Bighu Rural Municipality (All areas of ward no. 1)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 33.3828%;\" width=\"208\">\r\n<p>USD 20 per person/ week</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 10.9792%; text-align: center;\" width=\"60\">\r\n<p>8.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 55.638%;\" width=\"356\">\r\n<p>Gorkha Tsum Valley Area</p>\r\n<p>Sirdibas-Lokpa-Chumling-Chekampar-Nile-Chule</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Chumnubri&nbsp;&nbsp; Rural Municipality (All areas of wards nos. 3,6 and 7)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 33.3828%;\" width=\"208\">\r\n<p><strong>September &ndash; November:</strong></p>\r\n<p>USD 40 per person/week</p>\r\n<p>USD 7 per person/day (beyond 1 week)</p>\r\n<p><strong>December &ndash; August:</strong></p>\r\n<p>USD 30 per person/week</p>\r\n<p>USD 7 per person/day (beyond 1 week)</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 10.9792%; text-align: center;\" width=\"60\">\r\n<p>9.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 55.638%;\" width=\"356\">\r\n<p>Sankhuwasabha</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Bhotkhola Rural Municipality (All areas of wards no. 1 to 5)</li>\r\n<li>Makalu Rural Municipality (All areas of ward no. 4)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 33.3828%;\" width=\"208\">\r\n<p>USD 20 per person/ week (for the first 4 weeks)</p>\r\n<p>USD 25 per person /week (beyond 4 weeks)</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 10.9792%; text-align: center;\" width=\"60\">\r\n<p>10.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 55.638%;\" width=\"356\">\r\n<p>Solukhumbu</p>\r\n<p>Khumbu Pasang Lahmu Rural Municipality (All areas of ward no. 5)</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 33.3828%;\" width=\"208\">\r\n<p>USD 20 per person/ week (for the first 4 weeks)</p>\r\n<p>USD 25 per person /week (beyond 4 weeks)</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 10.9792%; text-align: center;\" width=\"60\">\r\n<p>11.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 55.638%;\" width=\"356\">\r\n<p>Rasuwa</p>\r\n<p>Gosaikunda Rural Municipality (All areas of ward no. 1 and some areas of ward no. 2)</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 33.3828%;\" width=\"208\">\r\n<p>USD 20 per person /week</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 10.9792%; text-align: center;\" width=\"60\">\r\n<p>12.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 55.638%;\" width=\"356\">\r\n<p>Manang</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Narpa Rural Municipality (All areas of wards no. 1 to 5)</li>\r\n<li>Nasho Rural Municipality (All areas of wards no. 6 and 7)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 33.3828%;\" width=\"208\">\r\n<p><strong>September &ndash; November:</strong></p>\r\n<p>USD 100 per person/week</p>\r\n<p>USD 15 per person/day (beyond 1 week)</p>\r\n<p><strong>December &ndash; August:</strong></p>\r\n<p>USD 75 per person/week</p>\r\n<p>USD 15 per person/day (beyond 1 week)</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 10.9792%; text-align: center;\" width=\"60\">\r\n<p>13.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 55.638%;\" width=\"356\">\r\n<p>Bajhang</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Saipal Rural Municipality (All areas of wards no. 1 to 5)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 33.3828%;\" width=\"208\">\r\n<p>USD 90 per person/week for the first week</p>\r\n<p>USD 15 per person/day (beyond 1 week)</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 10.9792%; text-align: center;\" width=\"60\">\r\n<p>14.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 55.638%;\" width=\"356\">\r\n<p>Mugu</p>\r\n<p>Mugumakarmarong Rural Municipality (All areas of wards no. 1 to 9)</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 33.3828%;\" width=\"208\">\r\n<p>USD 100 per person/week</p>\r\n<p>USD 15 per person/day (beyond 1 week)</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 10.9792%; text-align: center;\" width=\"60\">\r\n<p>15.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 55.638%;\" width=\"356\">\r\n<p>Darchula</p>\r\n<p>Vyas Rural Municipality (All areas of ward no. 1)</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 33.3828%;\" width=\"208\">\r\n<p>USD 90 per person/week</p>\r\n<p>USD 15 per person/day (beyond 1 week)</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em>Note: In the case of Upper Mustang and Upper Dolpa Region if the royalty paid for mountain expedition is less than the fee for the trekking permit then the difference amount should be paid.</em></p>', '1', '2022-07-17 07:53:19', '2022-07-17 07:54:39'),
(69, '22', '2. NATIONAL PARK / CONSERVATION AREAS PROJECT PERMITS', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Most of the trekking regions in Nepal are located either inside national parks or conservation areas. Trekkers are required to obtain these permits for most of the trekking trails in Nepal. FITs are allowed to trek inside the national parks or conservation areas. To obtain a trekking permit for these regions you need to fill up a form and submit it with a copy of your passport and passport size photo attached at the Nepal Tourism Board Office. This permit is issued by Nepal Tourism Board for trekking in Everest, Annapurna, Langtang, Manaslu, Mustang, and Rolwaling regions are some of the notable regions where you will need this permit.</p>\r\n<p>Where to get it: Nepal Tourism Board, Bhrikuti Mandap, Kathmandu</p>\r\n<p>Permit Cost:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><em>NPR 3,390 for National Park Permit</em></li>\r\n<li><em>NPR 3,000 for Conservation Area Permit per Trekker</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>3. TREKKING INFORMATION MANAGEMENT SYSTEM (TIMS)</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Trekkers Information Management System or in short TIMS is a permit implemented jointly by the Nepal Tourism Board (NTB) and Trekking Agencies Association of Nepal (TAAN). TIMS is implemented to ensure trekkers&rsquo; safety and security and control illegal trekking. This permit is required in all trekking regions of Nepal apart from the controlled area, where you will need a special permit. Group trekkers will have to obtain Blue TIMS cards by paying a fee of Rs 1,000 per person, while Free Individual Trekkers (FITs) have to get Green TIMS cards by paying a fee of Rs 2,000. Similarly, group trekkers from SAARC countries have to pay Rs 300 for TIMS cards, while FITs from the SAARC region have to pay Rs 600 each.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although the majority of the trekking regions in Nepal require a TIMS permit, the permit is only valid for the trekking area/route as mentioned in the permit.</p>\r\n<p>Where to get it: Nepal Tourism Board, Bhrikuti Mandap, Kathmandu</p>\r\n<p>Permit Cost: <em>NPR 2,000 per Trekker</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>4. RURAL MUNICIPALITY FEES</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A few rural municipalities have implemented that trekkers who are trekking inside these areas need a permit. These permits are issued at the starting point of the trek.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Where to get it: You can obtain this permit at the check post of the rural municipalities, such as Lukla, in the Everest region.</p>\r\n<p>Permit Cost:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><em>NPR 2,000 per trekker for Everest Region</em></li>\r\n<li><em>NPR 2,000 per trekkerfor Makalu Region</em></li>\r\n</ul>', '2', '2022-07-17 07:53:19', '2022-07-17 07:54:39'),
(70, '24', 'Passport and Visas', '<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\">Your passport must be valid for at least 6 months when you submit your APPLICATION for a visa.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-align: justify;\">\"On Arrival Visa\" can be obtained from all the entry points in Nepal. You can also get your visa from Nepalese Diplomatic Missions before your arrival. Some of the nationals require to get a visa before they arrive from their nearby Diplomatic missions of the Nepal Government. . You can find more details about visas for Nepal&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"https://www.sevensummittreks.com/info/visa-procedure-fees/visa-procedure-fees-for-nepal\">here</a>.<u><br /><br /></u></strong><u>\"Visa fees at the airport must be paid only in CASH, so make sure to carry enough cash to cover your visa fee at the immigration department.\"</u></p>', '1', '2022-08-08 06:19:25', '2024-06-20 03:49:02'),
(71, '24', 'Travel Insurance', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It is important to get proper insurance that covers medical expenses, emergency evacuation, and other travel protection required during the trip. Also, make sure that the insurance covers the level of activity you are going for. You can find more details about the insurance policy and the insurer <strong><a href=\"https://www.sevensummittreks.com/info/travel-advisory/travel-insurance\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">here</a>.</strong></p>', '2', '2022-08-08 06:20:53', '2023-09-14 09:31:32'),
(72, '24', 'Flights Confirmation Details', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It is better to know if your flight is on-time, sometimes there may be delays due to the weather condition or other unforeseen situations. If there is a delay in flights please notify us so we can manage your pick-up accordingly.</p>', '3', '2022-08-08 06:22:46', '2022-08-08 06:25:57'),
(73, '24', 'Equipment', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It is easy to travel with light baggage so make sure you only carry things that you need for your trip. Excess baggage means more weight and you may need to pay extra money if your baggage is heavier than the weight provided by the airlines. It will also be easier while you claim the baggage at the airport if you have single baggage rather than bringing many small bags.</p>', '4', '2022-08-08 06:22:46', '2022-08-08 06:25:57'),
(74, '24', 'Arrival Instruction at the Airport', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">After you arrive at the airport, proceed to the immigration to apply for Visa on Arrival if you haven\'t received a visa from your origin country, clear the customs charges if needed, and then collect your baggage and make your way to the arrival hall. You can get a SIM card at the arrival hall so that you don\'t have to find stores to get a Sim card later.</p>', '5', '2022-08-08 06:22:46', '2022-08-08 06:25:57'),
(75, '24', 'Airport Transfers', '<p>Upon your arrival at the airport, a representative from Seven Summit Treks will be waiting for you with our placard (Seven Summit Treks Banner). This representative is there to escort you to your hotel. We kindly request you to inform us about your arrival time and any potential delays. If you do not see our representative or our placard at the airport, please do not hesitate to contact us at <strong>+977 9801238848</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>Our contact details are provided <strong><a href=\"https://www.sevensummittreks.com/type-contact-us\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">here</a></strong>&nbsp;for your convenience.</p>\r\n<p>We are committed to ensuring your safety and satisfaction throughout your journey with us. We look forward to providing you with an unforgettable experience in the Himalayas.</p>\r\n<p>Safe travels!</p>', '6', '2022-08-08 06:22:46', '2024-02-05 08:21:17'),
(85, '24', 'Credit Cards', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">American Express, Master Card, and Visa are widely accepted at major hotels, shops, travel companies, and restaurants but a certain amount of service fee is charged by the banks. The clients must have a credit card with enough transaction limits available for any payment. Sometimes, cards are not acceptable or may not be applicable for enough transactions, so it is necessary to know the limits beforehand and contact your banks at the origin place for all the details required.</p>', '7', '2022-08-24 04:42:23', '2022-08-25 07:57:34'),
(88, '25', 'Inquiry', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">You can inquire about our expeditions and trekking packages through the \'Contact Us\", \'Inquiry\' or \'Book Now\' options available on the website and fill in the application form provided, afterward one of our expert team members will review your request and reply to you as soon as possible.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">With proper consultation with our expert, you can book the adventure you are interested in. We don\'t charge any kind of fee for a consultation.</p>', '1', '2022-08-24 06:30:34', '2022-08-25 04:35:40'),
(89, '25', 'Booking', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">After confirming to join our expedition or trekking, you are required to book a trip 3 months before the start of the trip to ensure maximum safety and satisfaction of the clients. In some extra cases, we also accept late bookings.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">You need to send us a copy of your passport after booking confirmation. Also, at least 30% of the total cost should be deposited during the time of booking or the amount that has been agreed during the correspondence has to be deposited as an advance.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Further, you will also be required to fill out a participation form. You can download the form provided <a href=\"https://www.sevensummittreks.com/storage/files/1/pDF/SST_Participation_Details.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>here</strong></a>.</p>', '2', '2022-08-24 06:30:34', '2022-08-25 06:42:36'),
(90, '2', 'Publicity', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: \'Calibri Light\',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: major-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: major-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: major-latin;\">Seven Summit Treks may request clients’ permission to use photographs and videos captured by clients, free of charge. Any materials provided will be used exclusively for marketing and promotional activities. Client privacy is paramount and will be strictly protected. We appreciate the clients’ cooperation in this matter.</span></p>', '18', '2023-01-26 06:16:57', '2024-08-16 07:40:34'),
(91, '24', 'Flight Schedule & Hotel Check-In', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A late-night or early-morning arrival (considered night) may incur additional charges for early check-in at the hotel. For example, most standard hotel check-in time is 3 PM but if you arrive around midnight then we have to book an extra night at the hotel or you have to wait till 3 PM to check in at the hotel.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It\'s important for travelers to be mindful of hotel check-in and check-out policies and to be prepared for any additional fees for early check-in or late check-out. Seven Summit Treks will do its best to arrange for early or late check-in/out requests, but travelers should also take into consideration the hotel\'s rules and room availability during busy seasons.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">So, travelers need to manage arrival time while booking their flights according to their itinerary.</p>', '8', '2023-02-10 04:06:35', '2023-08-25 09:27:07'),
(92, '24', 'Flight Ticket', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It is advisable to purchase a flexible return ticket, as the completion of the climbing expedition may occur ahead of schedule, depending on weather conditions and the progress made.</p>', '9', '2023-08-25 09:25:49', '2023-08-25 09:27:07'),
(93, '24', 'Bonus and Tips', '<p>All bonuses, tips, and other extra costs need to be paid in cash. So, members are required to bring cash for these expenses and not to be transferred to the company\'s account.</p>', '10', '2023-12-14 05:03:30', '2023-12-14 05:03:47'),
(94, '30', 'Booking in Advance and Payments', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">To ensure a safe and successful adventure with <strong>Seven Summit Treks Pvt. Ltd.</strong>, clients must book their trip at least three months in advance. This allows ample time for necessary preparations. Clients need to complete a company-provided form with their personal details for Chinese government approval at the time of booking. <strong>The Chinese government will then approve the name for the expedition permit. Clients must submit their original passport to our office in Nepal at least five days prior to their departure for China to facilitate the visa application process.</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A 30% deposit of the total trip cost is required upon booking to secure your reservation. This initial payment covers expenses such as hotel bookings, flights, guide and porter arrangements, and government permit fees. An additional 30% is due one month before departure, and the final 40% is payable before departure to China.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Bank Details:</u></strong></p>\r\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; height: 489.297px;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 54.3906px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 39.527%; height: 54.3906px;\" width=\"277\">\r\n<p><strong>Name of The Bank:</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 60.473%; height: 54.3906px;\" width=\"409\">\r\n<p>Himalayan Bank Ltd.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 63.7812px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 39.527%; height: 63.7812px;\" width=\"277\">\r\n<p><strong>Account Holder’s Name: (Beneficiary)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 60.473%; height: 63.7812px;\" width=\"409\">\r\n<p>Seven Summit Treks Pvt. Ltd.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 76.7812px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 39.527%; height: 76.7812px;\" width=\"277\">\r\n<p><strong>Account Number: (Beneficiary) USD $</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=