(825, 389, 'Pellot Maxime', 'maxime.pellot@hotmail.fr', '+33614224273', 'Dear Seven Summit Treks team : \r\n\r\nMy Name is Maxime Pellot and i\'m a 36 years old French man. \r\nI\'m very much interested in doing Baruntse Expedition during Spring 2023  and would like to know more about Seven summit treks programms for doing it. \r\n\r\nRegarding my Moutain experiences : I have been mountaineering in the French Alpes for more than 8 years now. Few 4000 pics such as \"Barre des écrins\" ; \"Castor & Polux\" and mostly lower altitude but more technical lines such as \"North face des Courtes during winter time - voies des suisses\" ; \"North face Tour ronde during winter time\" , \"ice chute Perroux delafosse on tour ronde during winter time\" etc ... Also i have been climbing for 8 years now, and feeling confortable in 6b (French grade) level and done few times ice climbing on ice fall in Italie and feeling confortable with grade 4. I only have one experience with high altitude which was in Bolivia (Chachacomani 6074 m) and i got good acclimations and no troubles with it. Also it was an easy summit ! \r\n\r\nI have the chance to have plenty of time from Begining of March to End of May 2023 so i could be very flexible if needed, and get the chance to adapt to high altitude before the climb by doing myself trekking around Baruntse summits. \r\n\r\n1st question: Is my Mountainering experience enough to undertake with you this expedition ? How many guide can we rely on during this expedition ? One by person or less ? \r\n\r\n2nd question: How many people has already registered for this expedition during Spring 2023 and how many do you need to validate the expedition ? \r\n\r\n3rd question: What kind of trek around Baruntse would you advised me to do by my self to get better acclimatization before undertaking with you Baruntse expedition\r\n\r\n4th question: What would be the price for doing this expedition ?\r\n\r\nBest regards Maxime', 'France', 0, '2023-02-06 22:31:00', '2023-02-06 22:31:00'),
